body_text.text:
All pigs were judged as clinically healthy and no gross lesions were observed (Table 2
). Microscopically, the pigs were judged as normal. However, minor histological lesions were noted in terms of occasional crypt abscesses, moderate lymphocyte infiltration of the lamina propria of villi in the ileum, and moderate epithelial hyperplasia in all segments of the gut (Fig. 1
).
